Show HN: A Search Engine for the Tildeverse
text:
The tildeverse is the name for a loose community of public access unix systems inspired by Paul Ford's famous tilde.club essay. These little communities are built up around shared access to a single unix system, utilizing its native multi-user properties almost as a retro social network.

Over time, the communities have grown and folks published handmade pages that have the vibe of the early WWW days. I built a search engine to let everyone find things on this quirky part of of the net.

Enjoy!
